cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.AI, cs.NEURAL 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks for the segmentation of anatomical structures in ultrasound volumes. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on medical imaging (cs.Medical Imaging) and proposes a novel architecture for semantic segmentation using convolutional encoder-decoder networks. The use of deep learning techniques for segmentation also falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NEURAL).
